# SwiftFormat configuration for MovieSwiftUI.
# Reference: https://github.com/nicklockwood/SwiftFormat/blob/main/Rules.md
#
# Optimized to preserve existing style: 4-space indent, K&R braces,
# DocC comments, no Xcode-template file headers. Designed to be safe
# to run with `./scripts/format.sh` without rewriting attribute /
# parameter layout the team already prefers.

# --- Swift version --------------------------------------------------------
--swiftversion 6.0

# --- What NOT to touch ----------------------------------------------------
# `.swiftformat` is treated as repo-root config; the format script targets
# `MovieSwift`, so `.build` and `DerivedData` are naturally outside scope.
# Skip asset catalogs and preview content explicitly anyway.
--exclude .build,DerivedData,**/Assets.xcassets,**/Preview Content

# --- Layout ---------------------------------------------------------------
--indent 4
--tabwidth 4
--smarttabs enabled
--maxwidth 140
--linebreaks lf
--trimwhitespace always
--ranges spaced
--operatorfunc spaced

# Preserve existing argument/parameter/return layout. The codebase uses a
# mix of styles depending on context (long Movie constructors fold over
# many lines, short SwiftUI initializers stay on one). Re-flowing them
# would churn a huge diff for negligible gain.
--wraparguments preserve
--wrapparameters preserve
--wrapcollections preserve
--wrapreturntype preserve
--wrapconditions preserve
--closingparen balanced
--commas inline

# --- Braces & spacing -----------------------------------------------------
--allman false
--elseposition same-line
--guardelse same-line
--emptybraces no-space

# --- Attribute placement --------------------------------------------------
# Preserve attribute placement; Swift Testing's `@Test func name()` and
# SwiftUI's `@Observable final class X` look fine inline, and pre-line
# `@MainActor` / `@Suite` decorators are kept where the author wrote
# them.
--funcattributes preserve
--typeattributes preserve
--varattributes preserve

# --- Self & access --------------------------------------------------------
--patternlet hoist
--self remove
--selfrequired
--stripunusedargs closure-only
--importgrouping testable-bottom
--marktypes always
--markextensions if-not-empty

# --- File headers ---------------------------------------------------------
# Project policy (CLAUDE.md): new .swift files must NOT include the Xcode
# template header block. Empty `--header` strips any existing block on
# format.
--header strip

# --- Disabled rules -------------------------------------------------------
# `wrapMultilineStatementBraces` would reflow K&R-style braces in some
# multi-line statements. `redundantReturn` removes `return` in single-
# expression bodies — the codebase mixes both styles intentionally
# (explicit `return` in trailing-closure builders for readability).
# `blankLinesAroundMark` adds blank lines around `// MARK:` comments,
# which the existing code rarely uses.
--disable wrapMultilineStatementBraces,blankLinesAroundMark,redundantReturn

# --- Enabled opt-in rules -------------------------------------------------
--enable isEmpty,sortImports,wrapEnumCases,markTypes
